The paper deals with the problem of pixelwise semantic labeling of images, specifically in the context of aerial and satellite images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to learn an iterative enhancement process for improving the quality of satellite image classification maps. This involves training the RNN on manually labeled data, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of partial differential equations, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of object localization, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
